text: River Tame is a Celtic river name, used in England to refer to: *River Tame, Greater Manchester, a river that meets the Goyt to form the Mersey *River Tame, West Midlands, the largest tributary of the Trent *River Tame, North Yorkshire, a tributary of the Leven and then the Tees ==See also== *River Tamar, a river that forms part of the border between Devon and Cornwall *River Thame, a river that flows through Buckinghamshire and Oxfordshire, a tributary of the Thames *River Thames, a river that flows through Oxford, Reading, and London
title: River Tame
